For some people Derek Forbes and Mick MacNeil *were* Simple Minds. Everything that was good about their signature sound came from those two amazing musicians. D Dorian is D E F G A B C D - it's the white notes on a piano starting on D. It's parent scale is C Major but it's better to think of it as a completley different world altogether: if you know the D Minor scale then you simply take the 6th note of that scale (Bb) and raise it a semitone (one-fret) to B. This works for any minor scale. I'm sure it was a typo but to confirm: C Dorian is actually C D Eb F G A Bb C and is derived from the Bb Major Scale.
